    	<part part_index="1" name="Nice—a beautiful city in France" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="200">
            	<![CDATA[
Nice (pronounced like the English word "niece") is the fifth largest city in France. It is like a magnet and attracts people from all over the world.
Nice's charm comes from its sunny weather and beautiful beaches. The city is well-known for the great view from the Promenade des Anglais (盎格鲁街).
The Promenade is a famous seaside walkway in Nice and runs for several miles. It has existed for a long time, dating back to the 1800s. Today, it is a famous tourist attraction and is home to many hotels, dozens of cafes and miles of beach. If you take a trip to Nice, you should not miss the Promenade. It is worth a visit even if you just plan to find a blue chair, have a seat, listen to the waves and enjoy the sunshine.
There are many other places to see in the city of Nice. Here are some of tourists' favorites：
◆ The Cours Selaya Flower Market (赛道塞拉亚花卉市场) is a must-see. It is also one of the main neighborhoods for dining. If you want to have seafood, it is the place to go. There are also many souvenir (纪念品) shops there.
◆ Cimiez (西米埃) is a hilltop neighborhood in Nice. It has a famous art museum. You can see many wonderful works of art in it.
    	]]>
            </article>
